fields.description:
As a Policy Central user I want to see a detail view so I can quickly pick from a variety of functions. 

Note - this story is intended to cover the page lay out. Individual components broken down further in other stories.

Three Roles:  Policy Manager, Accounting, Disbursement
Left nav display driven by rights.

The flash component should remain as part of Detail View. Flash component requires user name and pw.

Acceptance Criteria: 
* Users should see an option to make a payment 
* Users should see an option to view a specific policy - Policy View
* Users should have the ability to view Recent Activity
* Users should see an option to upload a document
* Users should see an option to add a note
* Users should see an option for Document Display
* Users should see an option to open support view
* Users should have an option for agent support
*

fields.description:
Current failure workfow for password reset

* Update users IxDirectory representation, IF succeeded move to next step in work flow ELSE fail
**   IF user exists in SageSure pxserver, THEN sync password, ELSE fail
**    IF user exists in FedNat pxserver, THEN sync password, ELSE fail

Ticket PPS-1355 is to create unique codes for each of these failure points. Each will need a unique error message.

If the failure is to update IxDirectory the message is "Your password has failed to be updated please contact a system administrator."

If the failure is to update SageSure pxserver the message is "You password has been updated but you may not have all of your previous SageSure access."

If the failure is to update FedNat pxserver the message is "You password has been updated but you may not have all of your previous FedNat access."
fields.summary: Update Password Reset Failure Messaging in Policy Central

fields.description:
Current failure logic when a password is updated

* Update users IxDirectory representation, IF succeeded move to next step in work flow ELSE fail
**   IF user exists in SageSure pxserver, THEN sync password, ELSE fail
**     IF user exists in FedNat pxserver, THEN sync password, ELSE fail


All three of these points of failure generate the same error message and that should not be the case. Each point of failure should have a unique failure code for the front end to decipher and render an appropriate error message.
